text:
Good place to catch up with friends or simply have a conversation with old timers. There's a wealth of wisdom speaking with the locals. There's that community vibe making the place feel welcoming.
Food is okay like in some hawker places.
Satay has the pineapple source which many other stalls don't provide anymore.  Mince meat noodles, provide fresh ingredients. Very nice 👍🏼👍👍🏾
Mixed rice very expensive 2 meat 2 veg $6.30 despite 1 meat 2 veg only cost $3.50
Value for money mixed rice. Generous portion. The salted egg chicken is really not bad and they use chicken pieces rather than cubes. 1 meat 1 egg 2 veg $4.50

Vegetarian bee hoon has a herbal taste which is unique.

but auntie is not exactly the friendliest, however polite you are.
